thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: All fir trees are evergreens. Some objects of worship are fir trees.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Some evergreens are not objects of worship.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
Fir(x) ::: x is a fir tree.
Evergreen(x) ::: x is an evergreen.
Worship(x) ::: x is an object of worship.
Premises:
∀x (Fir(x) → Evergreen(x)) ::: All fir trees are evergreens.
∃x (Worship(x) ∧ Fir(x)) ::: Some objects of worship are fir trees.
Conclusion:
∃x (Evergreen(x) ∧ ¬Worship(x)) ::: Some evergreens are not objects of worship.
